reviews.review:
Where it lack in pacing, the Rise of the Skywalker is a good conclusion to the forty years saga. 

For the heart felted fans of the series, it is a satisfying entry in the Star Wars predecessor and succeed to give more than most of them.

Overall, Rise of the Skywalker offer greats characters as well as building the universe even more than it was before, leaving the viewer with the craving of wanting more of Kylo Ren and Rey.
I was never a fan when I was a child but I enjoyed the experience of each movie with my children and I think this was the best one ( I'll duck now)
Didnâ€™t like how Lea told Rey to embrace who she was, and the end she denied being a Palpatine.

I loved this film, and I am not sure why it is getting panned by critics. All the loose ends were beautifully tied up, Carrie Fisher's passing was handled gently, there was as much nostalgia for those of us who were raised on Star Wars as needed. The space battles were epic. It was suspenseful, Rey's performance was masterful. They dealt with Adam Driver as best as they could have. It had everything I needed in the final film.

Personally I found rise of skywalker to be my favorite movie of the  Skywalker saga, I felt it was a good accumulation that tied together the previous 8 films, with great action, great trio vibes, great romance, all with that awesome galactic feel that we Star Wars fans love!
fantastic movie. I have been a SW fan for quite some time. That was a fitting end. I was engaged and the acting was solid across the board. Ignore any purists that refused to enjoy it.
Months of waiting, years of disappointment.
A true star wars movie, a fitting way to end the trilogy. Could have benefitted from maybe 15-30 more runtime but works fine as is

The storytelling is quite lacking and the chemistry between the characters is nonexistent. This is nothing like the original trilogy of movies that we all grew up to love as kids. This movie was made for millennials who have no attention span and need to have action all the time. Shame on Disney!
